subject: Cricket
lead_paragraph: An inquest into the death of the Pakistan cricket coach Bob Woolmer ended when a Jamaican jury was unable to determine the cause of death after hearing testimony from more than 50 people over five weeks. The 11-member panel deliberated for about four hours before returning an open verdict, which means jurors decided they had not heard sufficient evidence to declare Bob Woolmer’s death an accident, a homicide or the result of natural causes.
